<subSubSection id="C37565586413FFBBFF1AF7D84A9DC53D" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD036D36413FFBBFF1AF7D8485DC7E3" blockId="35.[189,303,412,438]" box="[189,303,412,438]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<heading id="D09881BF6413FFBBFF1AF7D8485DC7E3" bold="true" box="[189,303,412,438]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16413FFBBFF1AF7D8485DC7E3" bold="true" box="[189,303,412,438]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD036D36413FFBBFF1AF78E4A9DC53D" blockId="35.[187,1400,458,872]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
This species is rare in the studied material. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F4D506413FFBBFD00F78E4D57C7B1" authority="Wei, 1983" authorityName="Wei" authorityYear="1983" box="[679,1061,458,484]" class="Ostracoda" family="Bairdiidae" genus="Bairdia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beichuanensis">
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16413FFBBFD00F78E4AD9C7B1" box="[679,939,458,484]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Bairdia beichuanensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226413FFBBFC17F78E4D57C7B1" author="Wei M. &amp; Li Y. W. &amp; Jiang Z. W. &amp; Xie L. C." box="[944,1061,458,484]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="23 - 254" refId="ref34093" refString="Wei M., Li Y. W., Jiang Z. W. &amp; Xie L. C. 1983. Subclass Ostracoda. In: Chengdu Institute of Geology and Mineral Resources (ed.) Palaeontological Atlas of Southwest China, Guizhou. Volume of Microfossils: 23 - 254. Geological Publishing House, Beijing. [In Chinese.]" type="book chapter" year="1983">
Wei, 
<quantity id="4C979B366413FFBBFC4DF78E4D57C7B1" box="[1002,1061,458,484]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.03682" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" unit="in" value="1983.0">1983</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226413FFBBFBE1F78E4C4AC7B1" author="Song J. J. &amp; Gong Y. M." box="[1094,1336,458,484]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="117 - 127" refId="ref33247" refString="Song J. J. &amp; Gong Y. M. 2019. Ostracods from the Devonian - Carboniferous transition in Dushan of Guizhou, South China. Palaeobiodivsersity and Palaeoenvironments 99: 117 - 127. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12549 - 018 - 0322 - 7" type="journal article" year="2019">Song &amp; Gong (2019)</bibRefCitation>
from the Famennian and the Tournaisian of the Baihupo section, 
<collectingRegion id="49ABF8316413FFBBFCD6F7A94AABC452" box="[881,985,493,519]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
, South 
<collectingCountry id="F37876436413FFBBFB97F7A94D04C452" box="[1072,1142,493,519]" name="China" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226413FFBBFB22F7AA4C1EC45D" author="Song J. J. &amp; Gong Y. M." box="[1157,1388,494,520]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="117 - 127" refId="ref33247" refString="Song J. J. &amp; Gong Y. M. 2019. Ostracods from the Devonian - Carboniferous transition in Dushan of Guizhou, South China. Palaeobiodivsersity and Palaeoenvironments 99: 117 - 127. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12549 - 018 - 0322 - 7" type="journal article" year="2019">Song &amp; Gong 2019</bibRefCitation>
) does not belong to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F4D506413FFBBFE3AF4554BD1C47E" authorityName="Wei" authorityYear="1983" box="[413,675,529,555]" class="Ostracoda" family="Bairdiidae" genus="Bairdia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beichuanensis">
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16413FFBBFE3AF4554BD1C47E" box="[413,675,529,555]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Bairdia beichuanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as shown by the strong ventral and dorsal overlap and stocky morphology. Based on these characters, it is here reattributed to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F4D506413FFBBFC12F4704C00C41B" authority="Wang, 1988" authorityName="Wang" authorityYear="1988" box="[949,1394,564,590]" class="Ostracoda" family="Bairdiidae" genus="Bairdia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanbiancunensis">
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16413FFBBFC12F4704DA8C41B" box="[949,1242,564,590]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Bairdia nanbiancunensis</emphasis>
Wang, 1988
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226413FFBBFF19F4134822C424" author="Coen M." box="[190,336,599,625]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="311 - 317" refId="ref27682" refString="Coen M. 1989. Ostracodes of the Devonian Carboniferous transition beds of South China. Bulletin de la Societe belge de Geologie 98: 311 - 317." type="journal article" year="1989">Coen (1989)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F4D506413FFBBFE19F4134B4DC427" box="[446,575,599,626]" class="Ostracoda" family="Bairdiidae" genus="Bairdia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16413FFBBFE19F4134B65C424" box="[446,535,599,625]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Bairdia</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
from the Gelaohe Formation, Baihupo section, 
<collectingRegion id="49ABF8316413FFBBFBCCF4134DA1C424" box="[1131,1235,599,625]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
, South 
<collectingCountry id="F37876436413FFBBFA8EF4134C00C424" box="[1321,1394,599,625]" name="China" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">China</collectingCountry>
, Famennian. Following Olempska (1999), we consider that it belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F4D506413FFBBFBB2F43E4C48C4C1" authorityName="Wang" authorityYear="1988" box="[1045,1338,634,660]" class="Ostracoda" family="Bairdiidae" genus="Bairdia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanbiancunensis">
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16413FFBBFBB2F43E4C48C4C1" box="[1045,1338,634,660]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Bairdia nanbiancunensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The specimens shown in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226413FFBBFE1EF4DA4B3BC4ED" author="Coen M." box="[441,585,670,696]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="311 - 317" refId="ref27682" refString="Coen M. 1989. Ostracodes of the Devonian Carboniferous transition beds of South China. Bulletin de la Societe belge de Geologie 98: 311 - 317." type="journal article" year="1989">Coen (1989</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 2 gigs 2b, 3b) and in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226413FFBBFC2FF4DA4DF1C4ED" author="Song J. J. &amp; Gong Y. M." box="[904,1155,670,696]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="117 - 127" refId="ref33247" refString="Song J. J. &amp; Gong Y. M. 2019. Ostracods from the Devonian - Carboniferous transition in Dushan of Guizhou, South China. Palaeobiodivsersity and Palaeoenvironments 99: 117 - 127. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12549 - 018 - 0322 - 7" type="journal article" year="2019">Song &amp; Gong (2019</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5a) have a size similar to our material with respectively L = 1000–1100 µm, H = 650–675 µm, H/L = 0.59–0.67 and L = 1120µm, H = 706µm, H/L = 0.63. The specimen shown in Olempska (1999: fig. 29h) is as long as our biggest specimen and higher (L = 2310µm, H = 1540 µm, H/L = 0.67) but we consider that these differences are intraspecific variability. Three ontogenetic stages (A-2 to Ad) are present in our material; they only differ by the size without major changes throught ontogeny.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37565586413FFBBFF1AF5CB4D55C2FE" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="distribution">
