, Famennian–Tournaisian, late Devonian–early Carboniferous (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226413FFBBFD9DF2294A59C2D2" author="Song J. J. &amp; Gong Y. M." box="[570,811,1133,1159]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="117 - 127" refId="ref33247" refString="Song J. J. &amp; Gong Y. M. 2019. Ostracods from the Devonian - Carboniferous transition in Dushan of Guizhou, South China. Palaeobiodivsersity and Palaeoenvironments 99: 117 - 127. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12549 - 018 - 0322 - 7" type="journal article" year="2019">Song &amp; Gong 2019</bibRefCitation>
). Samples 19BAI 67, 19BAI 69, 19BAI 80, Blue Snake section, Gelaohe Formation, Famennian, late Devonian (this work).
